# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Tutorial 11: radiation damage cascade -- defect cluster analysis
#
# Re-analyze the final cascade configuration (final.dump): rebuild the
# perfect bcc reference lattice, overlay the defective positions, and use
# the per-cluster local output of compute frenkel to list every defect
# cluster with its size and center.  Negative sizes are vacancy clusters,
# positive sizes interstitial clusters.  No forces are needed for the
# static Wigner-Seitz analysis, so pair_style zero is used.

variable a0 equal 2.8553
variable nc equal 30

units metal
atom_style atomic
boundary p p p

lattice bcc ${a0}
lattice bcc 2.8553
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 2.8553 2.8553 2.8553
region box block 0 ${nc} 0 ${nc} 0 ${nc}
region box block 0 30 0 ${nc} 0 ${nc}
region box block 0 30 0 30 0 ${nc}
region box block 0 30 0 30 0 30
create_box 1 box
Created orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (85.659 85.659 85.659)
  1 by 1 by 1 MPI processor grid
create_atoms 1 box
Created 54000 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (85.659 85.659 85.659)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.003 seconds
mass 1 55.845
pair_style zero 5.0
pair_coeff * *

# overlay the defective configuration (match by atom ID, replace positions)
read_dump final.dump 15000 x y z box yes
Scanning dump file ...
Reading snapshot from dump file ...
  orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (85.659 85.659 85.659)
  54000 atoms before read
  54000 atoms in snapshot
  0 atoms purged
  54000 atoms replaced
  0 atoms trimmed
  0 atoms added
  54000 atoms after read

compute fr all frenkel
# one line per cluster: id, signed size, center (x, y, z)
dump cl all local 1 clusters.txt index c_fr[1] c_fr[2] c_fr[3] c_fr[4] c_fr[5]
dump_modify cl sort 1

thermo_style custom step c_fr[1] c_fr[2] c_fr[3]
run 0

